class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> memLeak(int memory1, int memory2) {
        int i = 1;
        while (memory1 >= i && memory2 >= i) {
            if (memory1 >= memory2) {
                memory1 -= i;
            } else {
                memory2 -= i;
            }
            i++;
        }
        return {i, memory1, memory2};
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(sqrt(max(memory1, memory2)))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iterates through each second, allocating memory to the stick with more available memory. The loop continues until one of the sticks does not have enough memory to allocate, at which point the program crashes and the function returns the crash time and remaining memory for each stick.

